title: PBS THE DINOSAURS The Death of the Dinosaurs 4 of 4.mpg
description:
The Dinosaurs!

The Death of The Dinosaur

Discover the startling facts and dramatic new theroies currently revolutionizing our understanding of some of teh largest, most ferocious animals ever walk the Earth, in THE DINOSAURS!  Banishing the once-accepted image of cold-blooded brutes plodding toward extincion, tantalizing new findings now show that active, fleet-footed hunters; others were devoted, family-rearing parents; and most heretical of all, warm-blooded!

On location with cutting-edge scientists unearthing the latest discoveries, and via dazzling, high-quality animation, this bold new series will forever change your view of these astonishing prehistoric overlords of the Earth!

"The Death of the Dinosar!" probes one of the most perplexing questions in all of science.  With and unrivaled record of world dominiation lasting highly diversified creatures could become extinct?   Beginning in 1980, Nobel-Prize-winning physicist Luis Alvarez and his son set out to prove that a massive comet or meteor was to blame.  Other scientists disagree, citing such alternative scenarios as violent volcanic activity or even a virulent dinosaur disease.  Whatever the answer, the mass-exteniction of dinosaurs did occur-and left a world ripe for habitation by a small, shrew-like mammal that would one day evolve into a new world-conquering species: homo-sapiens.

Running Time 60 mins.
